"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"cc74fc",
"children":[
"Symptoms and signs of bacterial meningitis include fever, nuchal rigidity, photophobia, and altered mental status."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s1_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4b1181",
"children":[
"CT of the head is indicated before proceeding with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"lumbar puncture",
"children":[
"LP"
]
},
" if signs or symptoms of increased intracranial pressure (papilledema, focal neurologic deficits, altered mental status, immunocompromise), history of ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"central nervous system",
"children":[
"CNS"
]
},
" disease (stroke, mass), or new-onset seizures are present."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_id_s1_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bf8567",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"cerebrospinal fluid",
"children":[
"CSF"
]
},
" Gram stain and cultures should be obtained, and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Streptococcus pneumoniae"
]
},
" antigen detection and multiplex ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"polymerase chain reaction",
"children":[
"PCR"
]
},
" assay should be performed, before antibiotic initiation."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ddfba9",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"The two most common organisms causing bacterial meningitis are ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"S. pneumoniae"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Neisseria meningitidis"
]
},
", accounting for >80% of cases."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s1_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_id_s1_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1b5980",
"children":[
"In patients treated empirically or with confirmed pneumococcal meningitis, adjunctive dexamethasone should be given with or before administration of antimicrobial agents and continued for 4 days."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5d2578",
"children":[
"Treatment of viral meningitis is symptomatic and supportive. Empiric antimicrobial agents may be initiated in viral meningitis until bacterial meningitis is excluded."
]
}
]
}
]
},
